Readability and maintainability: Neat and ordered code is simpler to read and comprehend. Indentation, commenting, and sensible variable names may make your code easier to read. This simplifies bug detection, code modifications, and expansion. This improves codebase maintainability and future development efficiency. Efficiency: Programming neatly and organizedly may boost your efficiency. Clear and orderly code makes it simpler to find faults, introduce new features, and comprehend the program's flow. Organizing your code makes it simpler to debug and fix problems. This may save time and boost productivity. In conclusion, being tidy and structured while programming enhances code readability, maintainability, and efficiency, making you a better programmer. 